<p />
<p />
Try a few of these using the simple examples you learned above. Write a simple test script of <code>globus-job-run</code> commands that checks if all these sites are working for you.
<p />
<h3><a name="Final_Review_Exercise"></a> Final Review Exercise </h3>
Pretend that "genr" is a compute intensive simulation program that you want to run on the Grid.  Your last task in this lab is to create 5 lists of 10 random numbers each: 1-digit numbers in the first file, 2-digit numbers in the second file, and so on.  
<p />
Since this work is "compute intensive", you want to run these jobs under the batch job manager at each site, <strong>not</strong> the fork job manager. Use either <code>jobmanager-pbs</code> or <code>jobmanager-condor</code>, according to the table above.  
<p />
And, of course, you want to do it all in parallel, in a script so that you can reproduce your results as needed.
<p />
<p />
<p />
<p />
